reviewText: I use to watch Strawberry Short Cake with my little sister when we were kids.  My daughter adores the show now.  Good clean cartoons.

I bought this video for my daughter as a potty training reward, after she saw the commercial for it on TV.  The video, which includes 3 episodes, was a hit from the start.  She loves the music, and we run around the house singing "sunshine girls."
My daughter just loved it.  It kept her entertained on a rainy day and teaches good morals besides. It was fun.
My daughter loves Strawberry and we have all of them...including this one now and it is worth it.  Cute as always!

This was a great DVD. MY daughters are BIG fans of this series and are always looking for new Strawberry Shortcake videos so having a DVD like this is great because it places all of their favorite characters at their fingertips. My eldest daughter said that this was an awesome DVD and she particularly enjoyed some of the fun things that happen throughout the DVD and the resort that Orange Blossom creates! All-in-all this was a great DVD and one that any Strawberry Shortcake fan will enjoy!

My four year old daughter is addicted to Strawberry Shortcake. I don't mind a bit. Strawberry and her friends are quite charming. I love that each episode usually involves a life lesson and how Strawberry always does the right thing. My little girl has learned a lot about manners, kindness, and how to treat friends through these episodes. I love the fact that I don't have to monitor her watching these DVD's. I'm quite strict about what she can watch that is age appropriate and Strawberry passes the test with flying colors.

This particular DVD contains three episodes and my daughter enjoys them as much as a full length movie. She actually prefers the multiple episodes. I think it helps her feel as she's watching more than one "movie."
